        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 2 at 7:57PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 756 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Marion Springs, or 10 miles west of St. Charles, moving northeast at
90 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Brant, Nelson, Essexville, Carrollton, Merrill, Garfield, Freeland,
Arthur, Munger, Auburn, Fenmore, Buena Vista Township, Gera,
Indiantown, Bridgeport, Swan Creek, Shiawassee National Wildlife
Refuge, Zilwaukee, Marion Springs, and St. Charles.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
